<tandem style="background-color:#333;" page="welcome" label="Getting Started">
  <style>
    .section {
      padding: 200px;
      color: rgba(240, 240, 240, 1);
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      line-height: 2em;
    }

    .section .instructions {
      margin-top: 200px;
    }

    p {
      margin: 40px 0px;
    }

    h1 {
      font-size: 42px;
      font-weight: 100;
    }

    strong {
      font-weight: 400;
    }

    h1::before {
      content: "> ";
    }

    code {
      background: #444;
      word-break: break-all;
    }

    .instructions {
      display: flex;
      font-family: Roboto, Helvetica;
      font-weight: 100;
      font-size: 14px;
    }

    .step {
      display: flex;
      position: relative;
      width: 1024px;
      height: 768px;
      margin-right: 200px;
    }

    .instructions .artboard {
      position: relative;
      width: 100%;
      height: 100%;
    }

    artboard {
      width: 100% !important;
      height: 100% !important;
    }

    .description {
      padding: 16px;
      word-wrap: break-word;
      width: 200px
    }
  </style>
  <div class="section">
    <h1>Integrating</h1>
    <div class="instructions">
      <div class="step">
        <div class="description">
          <!--p>Tandem comes with an IDE extension that offers a richer set of features such as realtime </p-->
          <p>Tandem's IDE extension enables you to design & hack on your application in real time.</p>

          <p>To install, search for "Tandem" in your default IDE extension pane. </p>  
        </div>
        <div class="artboard">
          <artboard src="./1-install-extension.html" title="Install IDE Extension"></artboard>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="step">
        <div class="description">
          <!-- TODO - docs for enabling source maps -->
          <p>1. Turn on source maps for JavaScript and CSS. Tandem needs that information in order to modify code.</p>
          <p>
            2. For <strong>Webpack</strong>, you can add the JSX loader (<code>npm install tandem-jsx-loader</code>) 
            which enables Tandem to modify JSX code (React, vue, etc). 
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="artboard">
          <artboard src="./2-setup-web-framework.html" title="Modify your Application Bundler (Webpack, SystemJS, etc.)"></artboard>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h1>Usage</h1>
    <div class="instructions">
      <div class="step">
        <div class="description">
          <p>1. Copy & Paste an Artboard that you'd like to see in a different size or browser.</p>

          <p>2. Modify the size & browser information the right panel.</p>

          <p>Tandem will launch a real browser instance via BrowserTap and render your Artboard's HTML & CSS against it.</p>

          <p>
            Source code change automatically synchronize across all Artboards that share the same document.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="artboard">
          <artboard title="Responsive & Cross-browser testing" src="./responsive-testing.html"></artboard>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="step">
        <div class="description">
          <p>
            You can inject any variable you want into the Window object of any Artboard. This includes the window location, navigator information, or any other custom property. 
          </p> 


          <p>
            1. Define a new Window global by selecting an Artboard and clicking the + button in the "Window Globals" panel. 
            Set first field to "message", and the second field to "Hola Mundo".
          </p> 


          <p>
            2. In the Artboard source file, write: <code>console.log(window.message);</code>.
            In the Tandem developer console pane, you should see "Hola Mundo" appear immediately. 
          </p> 

          <p>
            Tip: You can use the globals panel to define custom properties that reveal visual elements.
          </p>

        </div>
        <div class="artboard">
          <artboard title="Defining Artboard States" src="./artboard-states.html"></artboard>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="step">
        <div class="description">
          <p>Hold âŒ˜ while moving your mouse over any visual item in Tandem to reveal a link that will open the item source code in your IDE.</p> 

        </div>
        <div class="artboard">
          <artboard title="Linking back to source files" src="./link-to-source.html"></artboard>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="step">
        <div class="description">
          <p>
            Click the X button in the right hand side to share your workspace with other users. 
          </p> 

          <p>Tip: You can use your shared link to test how your HTML & CSS response on different devices.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="artboard">
          <artboard title="Sharing Workspaces" src="./sharing-workspace.html"></artboard>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</tandem>